   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb type="page" n="1"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <address>
                     <addrLine><placeName key="Washington">Washington. <choice>
                              <abbr>D. C.</abbr>
                              <expan>District of Columbia</expan>
                           </choice></placeName></addrLine>
                  </address>
                  <date when="1873-05-11">May 11th /73</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>My Dear <name key="Julia_C">Sister</name></salute>
            </opener>
            <p><persName key="Louisa_C" full="abb">Lulu</persName> sent me your letter I was ever so
               glad to hear from you And to hear you are all well <persName key="Louisa_C"
                  full="abb">Lulu</persName> has not been well for sometime but she is getting
               better. We are going to <choice>
                  <sic>movve</sic>
                  <corr>move</corr>
               </choice> to <placeName key="Westchester">Westchester</placeName> where <name
                  key="Uncle_G">Uncle Guss</name> live I am <choice>
                  <sic>goin</sic>
                  <corr>going</corr>
               </choice> to buy me a house there it a beautiful country village <measure unit="s"
                  commodity="hour" n="1">one hours</measure> ride from <placeName key="Philadelphia"
                  >Philadelphia</placeName> or is <measure unit="s" commodity="hour" n="4">four
                  hours</measure> ride from </p>
            <pb type="page" n="2"/>
            <p>
               <placeName key="NY">New York</placeName>. Grand Mother is still <choice>
                  <orig>a live</orig>
                  <reg>alive</reg>
               </choice> and bids fare to out live us all I will find out what she is worth and
               about what she intends to do with her property when she dies. <name key="Uncle_G"
                  >Uncle Guss</name> you know was her step son and <name key="Aunt">Aunt
                  Eliza</name> was her step daughter. It is a mixed up affair <name key="Uncle_G"
                  >Uncle Guss</name> and family are the nicest folks in the world. You remember
                  <name key="Uncle_E">Uncle Enoch Taylor</name> and sister Mother.used to think so
               much of they live in <placeName key="Jerman">Jerman Town</placeName>. We have <choice>
                  <orig>a bout</orig>
                  <reg>about</reg>
               </choice>
               <measure type="relationship" n="1700">17 hundred relations</measure>
               <choice>
                  <sic>liveing</sic>
                  <corr>living</corr>
               </choice> near <placeName key="Philadelphia">Philadelphia</placeName>. We had. </p>
            <pb type="page" n="3"/>
            <p>
               <note type="authorial" place="margin_top">I called on the <persName><roleName
                        key="President">President</roleName></persName> and family this evening and
                  am <choice>
                     <sic>invites</sic>
                     <corr>invited</corr>
                  </choice> to dine with him. That is Bout as near as I will ever come to live in
                  the <orgName key="WH">White House</orgName></note> a family diner while in
                  <placeName key="Philadelphia"><choice>
                     <abbr>Phila</abbr>
                     <expan>Philadelphia</expan>
                  </choice></placeName> and there were <measure commodity="people" n="42">42
                  persons</measure> to diner all Uncles Aunts Cousins half cousins and so forth They
               are all nice good people they liked to talked me to death about our family When I get
               rich I will have you <add place="inline" type="authorial">all</add> to come and see
               themâ€”; I was <choice>
                  <sic>goin</sic>
                  <corr>going</corr>
               </choice> to send some presents to you all But <persName key="Louisa_C" full="abb"
                  >Lulu</persName> said She <choice>
                  <sic>knowed</sic>
                  <corr>knew</corr>
               </choice> what to buy better than me so I left Her to do it but She writes me She has
               been to sick to attend to it but she </p>
            <pb type="page" n="4"/>
            <p> will send you something nice when she get well She says if I buy any thing it will
               be no good to you and the baby She wants to get something that will do you some good.
               I will <choice>
                  <sic>surly</sic>
                  <corr>surely</corr>
               </choice> pay you a visit this <date type="season">summer</date>. as I am <choice>
                  <sic>goin</sic>
                  <corr>going</corr>
               </choice> to go to <placeName key="Nebraska">Nebraska</placeName> for a hunt this
                  <date type="season">summer</date> I will <choice>
                  <sic>probaly</sic>
                  <corr>probably</corr>
               </choice> go to <placeName key="Europe">Europe</placeName> this <date type="season"
                  >fall</date>. By the time you answer we will <choice>
                  <sic>probaly</sic>
                  <corr>probably</corr>
               </choice> be <choice>
                  <sic>liveing</sic>
                  <corr>living</corr>
               </choice> in <placeName key="Westchester">Westchester</placeName>
               <choice>
                  <abbr>P.A.</abbr>
                  <expan>Pennsylvania Address</expan>
               </choice> so write me there </p>
            <closer>
               <salute>Your affectionate <name key="William_C">Brother</name></salute>
               <signed><persName key="William_C" full="abb">Will</persName></signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>Love to all</p>
            </postscript>
         </div>
